  "text": "The Kubernetes codebase (v1.32.0) contains comprehensive validation for pod security context fields across multiple layers. The primary validation mechanisms are:\n\n**runAsNonRoot Enforcement:**\nValidation occurs in staging/src/k8s.io/pod-security-admission/policy/check_runAsNonRoot.go through the CheckRunAsNonRoot() function and its implementation runAsNonRoot_1_0(). This enforces that containers must run as non-root users at the restricted security policy level. Runtime verification happens in pkg/kubelet/kuberuntime/security_context_others.go and pkg/kubelet/kuberuntime/security_context_windows.go (verifyRunAsNonRoot functions), which check the effective security context at container startup. Accessors for this field are provided in pkg/securitycontext/accessors.go.\n\n**Privileged Container Check:**\nPrivileged container restrictions are enforced through staging/src/k8s.io/pod-security-admission/policy/check_privileged.go (CheckPrivileged and privileged_1_0 functions) at the baseline security level. These checks ensure containers cannot set privileged=true. Additional validation occurs in pkg/apis/core/validation/validation.go within ValidateSecurityContext(), which verifies privileged mode against cluster policies. The Privileged() and SetPrivileged() accessors in pkg/securitycontext/accessors.go provide abstracted access to this field.\n\n**Capabilities Validation:**\nCapabilities are validated at two levels - baseline and restricted. The baseline level (staging/src/k8s.io/pod-security-admission/policy/check_capabilities_baseline.go) restricts added capabilities to a safe default set (AUDIT_WRITE, CHOWN, DAC_OVERRIDE, FOWNER, FSETID, KILL, MKNOD, NET_BIND_SERVICE, SETFCAP, SETGID, SETPCAP, SETUID, SYS_CHROOT). The restricted level (staging/src/k8s.io/pod-security-admission/policy/check_capabilities_restricted.go) requires ALL capabilities to be dropped and permits only NET_BIND_SERVICE. API-level validation is performed in pkg/apis/core/validation/validation.go. The Capabilities() and SetCapabilities() accessors in pkg/securitycontext/accessors.go manage this field.\n\n**Seccomp Profile Enforcement:**\nSeccomp profile validation spans multiple files. The baseline policy (staging/src/k8s.io/pod-security-admission/policy/check_seccompProfile_baseline.go) validates both legacy annotations and the seccompProfile field. The restricted policy (staging/src/k8s.io/pod-security-admission/policy/check_seccompProfile_restricted.go) enforces that only RuntimeDefault and Localhost profiles are allowed, with special handling for Windows pods from v1.25+. Core validation functions in pkg/apis/core/validation/validation.go include validateSeccompProfileField(), validateSeccompProfileType(), ValidateSeccompProfile(), and ValidateSeccompPodAnnotations(). The SeccompProfile() and SetSeccompProfile() accessors provide field access abstraction.\n\nAll these validations are organized through the pod security admission framework, which applies policy checks at different enforcement levels (Baseline, Restricted) and versions, ensuring backward compatibility while enforcing increasingly strict security requirements."
}

